## Auto-Review: All Changes on Branch `task-auto-execute-afk-1782620000414`

**Scope reviewed**: 56 files changed (~6872 lines added, 66 removed). I reviewed every source-code change (TypeScript/TSX, CSS, config, scripts) across 19 source files. Configuration, documentation, issue templates, and infrastructure scripts were checked for correctness but not subjected to the same depth of code-review scrutiny.

---

### Security Issues

| # | File:Line | Description | Severity |
|---|-----------|-------------|----------|
| S1 | `.devflow/config.yaml:24` | **Telegram bot token hardcoded in plaintext.** The token `8664047075:AAFzMlQ9Ab5liRBaKOZFWo1HrfbmNzADZec` is committed in `.devflow/config.yaml`. Anyone with repo access can use this token to send messages as the bot and potentially access the bot's chat history. | **HIGH** |
| S2 | `.devflow/scripts/notify.py:41` | **Telegram API key transmitted over cleartext connection.** The `urllib.request.urlopen` call to `api.telegram.org` is HTTPS-only, but the bot token is included verbatim in the URL path (`url = f"https://api.telegram.org/bot{bot_token}/sendMessage"`). This is the standard Telegram API pattern, so the immediate concern is the plaintext credential in the config file (S1). | **HIGH** (linked to S1) |
| S3 | `packages/web/src/components/TerminalView.tsx:131` | **Clipboard API called without `navigator.clipboard` capability check.** The `navigator.clipboard.writeText()` call is not wrapped in a try/catch and does not check `navigator.clipboard` existence. On non-HTTPS origins or in some embedded webviews, this will throw an unhandled promise rejection. | **MEDIUM** |
| S4 | `packages/web/src/stores/lobby-store.ts:222` | **`ptyOutputListeners` stores single callback per session — any component can overwrite another's listener.** If two components ever call `registerPtyOutputListener` for the same sessionId, the second silently replaces the first with no warning. This is a misuse/race risk, not a direct security hole, but in the context of an application that may forward terminal output (including credentials typed into terminals), a stomped listener could lead to missed data routing. | **LOW** |

### Performance Issues

| # | File:Line | Description | Severity |
|---|-----------|-------------|----------|
| P1 | `packages/web/src/App.tsx:38-68` | **Excessive granular Zustand selectors.** Each of 14+ individual `useLobbyStore((s) => s.X)` selectors triggers a separate store subscription. Zustand uses shallow comparison, so the re-render overhead is minimal, but this pattern adds 14+ re-render checks on every store update. A single selector with destructuring or a multi-selector pattern would be more efficient. | **LOW** |
| P2 | `packages/web/src/components/Sidebar.tsx:44-46` | **`agentName` selector runs a linear scan on every store change for every SessionCard.** The `useLobbyStore((s) => { ... s.agents.find(...) ... s.deletedAgents.find(...) })` inside a reactive callback means every SessionCard re-evaluates both `agents.find` and `deletedAgents.find` on any store change, not just changes to the specific agent. This is `O(n)` per SessionCard per store update. For large agent lists with many sessions, this scales poorly. | **MEDIUM** |
| P3 | `packages/web/src/App.tsx:73-82` | **`matchMedia` listener registered unconditionally, not just on mobile.** The `useEffect` runs on every mount regardless of viewport. On desktop-only usage (never resized), this is a one-time cost that is negligible, but the `MediaQueryListEvent` handler fires on every viewport resize, calling `setDrawerOpen(false)` each time. This could cause unnecessary state updates on desktop when side-by-side window snapping. | **LOW** |
| P4 | `packages/web/src/stores/lobby-store.ts:582-584` | **`registerPtyOutputListener` always creates a new object in the store.** Every call to `registerPtyOutputListener` spreads the existing `ptyOutputListeners` object to create a new one, even if the listener function reference is identical to the existing one. Since listeners are closures created inside `useEffect`, they are new references every render, so this isn't practically avoidable — but the pattern is worth noting. | **LOW** |

### Maintainability Issues

| # | File:Line | Description | Severity |
|---|-----------|-------------|----------|
| M1 | `packages/web/src/components/TerminalView.tsx:19` | **Module-level mutable cache (`terminalCache` Map) is never cleaned up.** The `Map<string, CachedTerminal>` persists terminal instances indefinitely. When sessions are removed, the corresponding terminal DOM element is detached but the `Terminal` object, `FitAddon`, and all their event listeners remain in memory permanently. This is a memory leak that grows with each distinct `sessionId` ever mounted. | **HIGH** |
| M2 | `.devflow/archon/auto-execute-afk.yaml:85` | **Hardcoded API proxy URL with authentication token.** `ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL=http://localhost:3457` with `ANTHROPIC_AUTH_TOKEN=sk-maf-hub-mini-router` and `ANTHROPIC_MODEL=qwen3.7-max[1m]` are embedded in the workflow YAML. The `[1m]` suffix on the model name appears to be a typo (likely `[1m]` is an ANSI escape code or mistaken suffix for `--max-turns`). | **MEDIUM** |
| M3 | `packages/web/src/components/MobileDrawer.tsx:15-43` | **Class component `ErrorBoundary` uses instance method for retry created in `handleRetry`.** The `handleRetry` property is initialized as a class field arrow function. While functional, this is inconsistent with the rest of the codebase which uses functional components with hooks. Additionally, the retry just calls `onClose()` (closing the drawer) rather than actually re-mounting the errored children — meaning the user closes the drawer, opens it again, and the ErrorBoundary still shows `hasError=true` until the Sidebar component tree is unmounted (which only happens once per session). | **MEDIUM** |
| M4 | `packages/web/src/components/Sidebar.tsx:163` | **Hardcoded adapter abbreviation mapping.** The ternary chain `session.adapterName === 'claude-code' ? 'CC' : ... === 'codex-cli' ? 'CX' : ... === 'opencode' ? 'OC' : ... === 'gsd' ? 'GSD' : session.adapterName` is brittle — every new adapter requires updating this chain. Should use a lookup map or derive from backend metadata. | **MEDIUM** |
| M5 | `.devflow/scripts/notify.py:19-28` | **Naive YAML parser cannot handle quoted/escaped values.** The `load_config` function splits on `:` and takes the rest as the value. A value containing `:` (e.g., a URL or a token starting with a scheme like `http:`) would break. The token doesn't, but the pattern is fragile. | **LOW** |
| M6 | `.devflow/scripts/check_constitution.py:10-13` | **Import error silently falls through to JSON output.** If `python-frontmatter` or `yaml` are missing, the script prints a JSON error and exits. The JSON output is consumed by `dispatch.sh` (line 70), which tries to parse it. If the script exits with code 1 before the JSON is consumed correctly, the error message `python3 -c "import json,sys; d=json.load(sys.stdin); print(d.get('failed',0))"` will fail because the piped input is still the error JSON — but the error message is also printed to stdout, so parsing may work anyway. Fragile but functional. | **LOW** |
| M7 | `packages/web/src/App.tsx:18` | **Unused imports: `DiscoverDialog`.** Looking at the diff context, `DiscoverDialog` is imported but I need to verify it's actually used. Reading the current App.tsx, line 198-200: `{showDiscoverDialog && (<DiscoverDialog ... />)}` confirms it IS used. No issue. | (Resolved) |
| M8 | `packages/web/src/components/Sidebar.tsx:203` | **`versionInfo` is fetched from `useVersionCheck()` but only `hasUpdate` and `latest` are used.** The `versionInfo` object is destructured implicitly via `versionInfo.hasUpdate` and `versionInfo.latest` on lines 408-416. The variable is also declared on line 203. This is fine — no unused variable. | (Resolved) |
| M9 | `packages/web/src/components/Sidebar.tsx:216-220` | **`useEffect` for `agentsPanelRequest` has missing dependency.** The effect `useEffect(() => { if (agentsPanelRequest) { setShowAgentsPanel(true); } }, [agentsPanelRequest]);` is missing `setShowAgentsPanel` in the dependency array. Since the setter function from Zustand is stable (never changes reference), this won't cause bugs in practice, but it violates the React `exhaustive-deps` rule. | **LOW** |
| M10 | `.devflow/archon/dispatch.sh:119` | **`sed` pattern may match wrong branch name.** The pattern `s/^status: in_progress$/status: in_review/` is applied without checking that the branch hasn't changed between `git pull --rebase` and the `sed` call. On line 118, a `git pull --rebase` is done, which could introduce concurrent changes to the issue file (e.g., from another dispatcher or reconciler). If the status was already changed by another process, the sed silently does nothing, and the subsequent commit/push would be a no-op. This is handled by the error check on line 122 (`git push 2>/dev/null || log "WARN: push 失败"`), but the race window is real. | **LOW** |
| M11 | `packages/web/src/stores/lobby-store.ts:231-237` | **Module-level mutable state (`seenIdsBySession`) is never cleaned up for removed sessions.** The `removeSession` action (line 383-395) calls `delete seenIdsBySession[id]`, so this IS cleaned up. Verified — no issue. | (Resolved) |
| M12 | `.devflow/scripts/notify.py:39` | **Hardcoded message length limit without warning.** `text = text[:4000]` silently truncates messages over 4000 characters. For long approval requests with many changed files, the file list will be silently truncated. | **LOW** |
| M13 | `.devflow/archon/dispatch.sh:129` | **`FILES` variable with brace substitution in Python embedded string.** The line `FILES=$(git diff --name-only HEAD~1 2>/dev/null | head -20 | tr '\n' ',' | sed 's/,$//')` then interpolates `'${FILES}'` into a Python heredoc. If `FILES` contains special characters (single quotes, backslashes), the inline Python string will break. The brace substitution in the Python f-string (`'${FILES}'`) is not escaped. | **LOW** |

